      "configuration": {
        "config$prompt": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "Objective: Use the text generation capability to define high-precision astronomical algorithms and logic for calculating planetary positions similar to Swiss Ephemeris. Subsequently, generate and execute Python code to perform these calculations using the provided date, time, and location details to determine coordinates such as longitude, latitude, and distance for celestial bodies.\n\nOutput Format: Provide the generated logic instructions and the resultant planetary data produced by the Python script. Use the system_objective_fulfilled tool once the results are displayed.\n\nUser Input / Context:\nDate: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_date\",\"title\":\"Date\"}}\nTime: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_time\",\"title\":\"Time\"}}\nLocation: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_location_details\",\"title\":\"Retrieve Precise Location Information\"}}"
